---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../../components/PageHeader.astro";
import Section from "../../components/Section.astro";
import { link } from "../../utils/link";

const LAST_UPDATED = "2026-04-14";
const IMPRINT_HREF = link("/legal/imprint");
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Premium TV Player"
  description="What Premium TV Player collects, why, where it's stored, and how you can delete it."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    lede={`Last updated: ${LAST_UPDATED}. This page is a plain-language summary of what we collect, why, and how to remove it. Our legal team will finalize the binding text before launch.`}
  />

  <Section>
    <article class="legal-body">
      <p class="legal-callout">
        <strong>TL;DR.</strong> We collect the bare minimum needed to run the app:
        your email, a Firebase user ID, your entitlement status, and the URLs
        of the sources you add (encrypted). We don't serve ads, we don't sell
        data, and we don't build advertising profiles.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-title-large">1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Premium TV Player ("the App", "we", "us") is an independent project
        operated by <strong>Belkis Aslani</strong> (the "Operator"),
        based in Freiberg am Neckar, Germany. A sole-proprietor business
        registration is currently in progress. Full contact details are
        published on the <a href={IMPRINT_HREF}>Imprint</a> page.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-title-large">2. Data we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account data.</strong> Email address and a Firebase UID, used to sign you in and associate your purchases with your account.</li>
        <li><strong>Entitlement status.</strong> Whether your account is on trial, Lifetime Single, Lifetime Family, expired or revoked, plus the Google Play purchase token for refund / revocation handling.</li>
        <li><strong>Profiles.</strong> Profile name, whether it is a Kids profile, age-rating cap, and an optional PIN (stored only as an Argon2id hash).</li>
        <li><strong>Sources.</strong> The URLs, usernames, passwords and custom headers for the M3U / M3U8 / XMLTV feeds you add. All credential fields are encrypted at rest with AES-256-GCM and a fresh IV per write.</li>
        <li><strong>Library state.</strong> Your watch history, favorites, and Continue Watching positions — scoped to the profile you're using.</li>
        <li><strong>Device metadata.</strong> A hashed device token, device model, OS version, and last-seen timestamp, used for device-slot management.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="t-title-large">3. What we do not collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising SDKs. No ad impressions, no click tracking, no cross-app identifiers.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> bind your account to a MAC address or to any hardware identifier the OS hasn't explicitly handed us.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> record the specific streams or programmes you watch — we record the show you were watching per profile, so Continue Watching works, and we record aggregate watch history. We do not sell, share or export this.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> have access to the content of your sources. We parse the playlist / EPG structure, that's it.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="t-title-large">4. Sub-processors</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google (Firebase Authentication).</strong> Handles sign-up / sign-in / password reset. Governed by Google's Firebase Data Processing Terms.</li>
        <li><strong>Google (Play Billing).</strong> Processes purchases and refund events. Governed by Google's Play Developer Distribution Agreement.</li>
        <li><strong>Our own hosted infrastructure.</strong> PostgreSQL + Redis in the EU. No other third-party data processor is in the loop.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="t-title-large">5. Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Account and library data is kept while your account exists. When you delete your
        account from inside the app, profiles, sources, watch history and PINs are deleted
        within 30 days. Firebase sign-in records are deleted at the same time via the
        Firebase Admin SDK. Encrypted backups may retain a hashed copy for up to 90 days
        for disaster recovery, after which they are purged.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-title-large">6. Your rights (GDPR)</h2>
      <p>
        If you are in the EU / EEA / UK, you have the right to access, correct, port and
        delete your personal data under the GDPR. You can exercise all of these rights
        directly from the <em>Settings → Account</em> screen in the app. For anything that
        isn't self-service, email the address on the <a href={IMPRINT_HREF}>Imprint</a> page.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-title-large">7. Children</h2>
      <p>
        Premium TV Player is rated for general audiences but is not directed at children
        under 13. The Kids profile is a parental-controls feature — it does not imply the
        service is designed for children as its primary audience. Accounts are created by
        the device owner, not by children.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-title-large">8. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        When we update this policy, we bump the "Last updated" date at the top of this page
        and, for material changes, surface an in-app notice the next time you open the app.
      </p>

      <p class="legal-footer">
        Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}.
      </p>
    </article>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-body {
    max-width: 780px;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-l);
  }
  .legal-body h2 { margin: var(--space-l) 0 0; color: var(--color-on-surface-high); }
  .legal-body p, .legal-body li { margin: 0; color: var(--color-on-surface); }
  .legal-body ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-s); }
  .legal-body a { color: var(--color-accent-cyan); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .legal-callout {
    padding: var(--space-l);
    border-radius: var(--radius-m);
    border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3);
    background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08);
  }
  .legal-footer { color: var(--color-on-surface-muted); }
</style>
